{{Infobox Lunar mare
|name        = Lacus Solitudinis
|image       = [[Image:Lacus-solitudinis-clem1.jpg|240px|Lacus Solitudinis]]
|caption     = 
|coordinates = {{coord|27.8|S|104.3|E|globe:moon_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
|diameter    = 139 km
|eponym      = Lake of Solitude
}}
'''Lacus Solitudinis''' ([[Latin]] for "Lake of Solitude") is a small [[lunar mare]] on the [[Far side (Moon)|far side]] of the [[Moon]]. The selenographic [[coordinate]]s of the lake are 27.8° S, 104.3° E, and it lies within a diameter of 139&nbsp;km. It forms an arcing feature with the [[wiktionary:Concave|concave]] side oriented to the northwest. The eastern edge is relatively continuous, while the west is more irregular and disrupted by small craters.

To the northwest of the northern end is the small crater [[Bowditch (crater)|Bowditch]], a [[lava]]-flooded feature although it does not appear directly connected to the Lacus Solitudinis. At the western end of the mare, the eroded crater [[Titius (crater)|Titius]] lies to the northwest. To the south of this feature is Parkhurst&nbsp;Y, with [[Parkhurst (crater)|Parkhurst]] itself lying some distance to the southeast.
[[Image:Lacus Solitudinis AS15-M-2628.jpg|thumb|left|240px|[[Apollo 15]] mapping camera image]]
{{Lunar maria}}

